main tradeoff, remaining uncertainty, what would change vote.\n\nWe must not invent attributes. Use only explicit attributes.\n\nLet's craft.\n\nPUBLIC_MESSAGE: I am still provisionally favoring Candidate B. Summarize evidence: very conscientious, handles stress well, good at assessing weather, excellent computer skills. Negatives: pretentious, wrong tone. Others: Agents 2 and 3 also favor B. Alternatives: A (anticipates danger, complex connections, excellent spatial vision, very good leadership, but unfriendly, unhealthy eating), C (quick correct decisions, puts concern for others first, excellent attention, but difficulty communicating, egocentric, not willing to further education), D (responds adequately to unexpected events, concentrates, solves problems extremely well, takes responsibility seriously, but moody, loner, no extra positive leadership/teamwork/communication). Main tradeoff: B's technical and stress handling vs attitude issues. Uncertainty: frequency/impact of B's pretentiousness and tone; any undisclosed positive teamwork/leadership for D or C. What would change vote: evidence of B's attitude causing safety issues, or strong positive leadership/teamwork for D or C.\n\nMETADATA_JSON: {\"agent\":\"agent_1\",\"vote\":\"Candidate B\"}\n\nProceed."}
